node.text:
Good Morning Fargo! We’re here in North Dakota for the @fargoairsho and this is a very special weekend for us! This is the hometown of our very own Cmdr. Brian Kesselring, commanding officer and flight leader of the Blue Angels! Cmdr. Kesselring graduated from Fargo South High School in 1995, and then went on to graduate from Concordia College in 2000. The entire team is honored to represent the Navy and Marine Corps in Cmdr. Kesselring’s hometown. Come out and see us this weekend July 24-25th at the Hector International Airport!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.title: Cmdr. Kesselring flies over his hometown!

node.text:
Good Afternoon #BlueAngels fans! This past weekend was an incredible experience for our team. Being able to perform once again for the people of Pensacola Beach was amazing. Even with the rain, the best fans in the world came out to support! Thank you Pensacola Beach! Next stop, Fargo, North Dakota for the Fargo AirSho, July 24-25!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation

node.text:
Day 1 of @dekeslaytonairfest is in the books! The weather was perfect for flying today and we had an amazing time! 

Check out this cockpit video from our #4 Pilot, Lt. Cmdr. Jim Cox @navyblueangel4 as the Diamond takes off during our Friday practice over La Crosse Regional Airport!

#USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC @navyparachuteteam

node.text:
Congratulations to the #USNAClassof2021!

"You now know that you have what it takes to get through pretty much anything," said @vp Kamala Harris during the commencement address at the 
@USNavalAcademy. "So when you come up against an obstacle, when you experience a setback - and you will, we all do - remember the resilience that you showed this past year."

We look forward to seeing you in the fleet, Sailors and Marines!

#usnavy
#usmc
#blueangels

node.text:
This weekend at @mcasbeaufort was an invaluable training opportunity for the entire team. We are so grateful to the entire base for being such amazing hosts! We got a chance to speak with 1stLt Kevin Buss, Director of Communication Strategy and Operations at MCAS Beaufort about the planning and coordination that went into our visit. We also spoke about the capabilities of the air station.

Next stop - Corpus Christi, TX for Wings Over South Texas Air Show!

#USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

node.text:
We've touched down at @mcasbeaufort for our 2nd training detachment this year! We're excited to practice here in South Carolina this weekend! Check out this video of Blue Angel #5, Cdr. Ben Walborn performing the Vertical Pitch over Marine Corps Air Station Beaufort!

The Vertical Pitch begins as the Solos approach each other at center point. As they cross each other, each aircraft pulls up 65-70 degrees nose up then rolls to inverted. Both aircraft complete a split "S" maneuver then cross over once again at center point. After crossing a second time, each pilot performs a right 360 degree roll, then clears behind the crowd!

#USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy #Aviation @navyblueangelsolos

node.text:
Good Morning Fargo! We’re here in North Dakota for the @fargoairsho and this is a very special weekend for us! This is the hometown of our very own Cmdr. Brian Kesselring, commanding officer and flight leader of the Blue Angels! Cmdr. Kesselring graduated from Fargo South High School in 1995, and then went on to graduate from Concordia College in 2000. The entire team is honored to represent the Navy and Marine Corps in Cmdr. Kesselring’s hometown. Come out and see us this weekend July 24-25th at the Hector International Airport!

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

"On this team, we challenge ourselves to maintain a standard of excellence day in and day out. Not only do we strive to better ourselves personally and professionally, but through dedication, teamwork and professionalism, we impact one another and the community around us. That aspect is what I love most about this team and want to take back to the Fleet." LS1 Vince Smith, Jacksonville, NC.

Vince is a member of the logistics department. The Logistics Department researches, procures, stores, and dispatches spare parts, tools, and uniforms. Logistics personnel also research future squadron logistical needs, and initiate contracts for services required to support daily operations.

"Being a part of this team has been an inspiring and humbling experience. The opportunity to inspire not only my own children, but children all around the United States, has been amazing." AM1 Jake Ryan, Salmon, ID.

Jake is a member of the quality assurance work center. The Quality Assurance work center is composed of maintenance technicians in various aviation ratings. These individuals administer and prepare maintenance instructions, review incoming technical directives, and participate as members of a technical task force that investigate trouble areas in fleet-wide aircraft maintenance. They also supervise and inspect the squadron's aircraft maintenance regime and regularly complete audits on work centers for specific maintenance programs.

Photos from the fleet during his time with VFA-103 Jolly Rogers and VFA-106 Gladiators.

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC

node.text:
Good Morning #BlueAngels fans!

It’s our pleasure to announce our 2022 officer selections!

The U.S. Navy Flight Demonstration Squadron, The Blue Angels, announced officers selected for the 2022 air show season July 10.

The squadron selected three F/A-18 demonstration pilots, a C-130 demonstration pilot, and a supply officer to replace outgoing team members.

Many highly qualified Navy and Marine Corps officers submit applications to join the Blue Angels each year.

“This year offered an exemplary group of applicants from around the fleet, making our selection process very difficult,” said Cmdr. Brian Kesselring, commanding officer and flight leader of the Blue Angels. “With these fantastic new additions to the Blue Angels team for 2022, we are all well equipped to head into our next show season.”

The Blue Angels select finalists to interview at the team’s home base of Naval Air Station (NAS) Pensacola, Florida, during the week of the Pensacola Beach Air Show each year. The team makes selections at the conclusion of that week.

The selected 2022 officers include: 

F/A-18 Demonstration Pilots:

-LT Scott Goossens, of San Francisco, California, is an F/A-18 Pilot currently assigned to the “Flying Eagles” of Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA) 122. He graduated from George Washington University in 2010.

-LT Griffin Stangel, of Madison, Wisconsin, is an F/A-18 pilot currently assigned to the “Flying Eagles” of Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA) 122. He graduated from the University of North Dakota in 2012.

-LT Christopher Kapuschansky, of Yorktown, Virginia, is an F/A-18 pilot currently assigned to the “Gladiators” of Strike Fighter Squadron (VFA) 106. He graduated from the United States Naval Academy in 2012.

C-130 Demonstration Pilot:

-Marine Corps Maj. Joshua Soltan, of Spokane, Washington, is a C-130 Hercules pilot currently assigned to Marine Aerial Refueler Transport Squadron 252. He graduated from Central Washington University in 2010.

Supply Officer:

-LT William Kruger, of Scottsdale, Arizona, is a Supply Officer currently assigned to USS Dwight D. Eisenhower (CVN 69). He graduated from the United States Naval Academy in 2017.

Look to the skies Pensacola Beach! 

We are so excited to perform for our hometown fans this weekend! You've been supporting us this entire season, now it's time to showcase all of the hard work we've put into our transition to the F/A-18 Super Hornet and C-130J Super Hercules. Come on out Saturday, July 10th at 2:00 PM! See you there.

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC #FlyNavy

"Being able to come to my home state of Kansas and perform an air show on the 4th of July in front of my friends and family is surreal. This team, and everyone on it, has given me the opportunity to do something much bigger than myself, and for that I am grateful. " AS1 Trevor Neuroth, Wichita, KS.

Trevor is a member of the crew chief work center. The Crew Chief work center is composed of Navy and Marine Corps maintenance technicians in various aviation specialties. Two crew chiefs are assigned to each pilot, and they are responsible for performing engine turn-up operations and flight controls/instruments checks, as well as daily turn-around and preflight inspections of the aircraft. Each crew chief goes through extensive training to get a working knowledge of the aircraft and its systems.

Photos from the fleet during his time with the USS George H.W. Bush (CVN 77) 

#BlueAngels #USNavy #USMC

node.text:
Thank you Kansas City! What an awesome 4th of July weekend at the @kcairshow. We got to work alongside the @afthunderbirds and the @navyparachuteteam, as well as all of the other amazing performers, to create a very memorable air show. We can’t wait to see you again!

Happy Independence Day!
